Congressman Alcee Hastings was known for his warmth, good humor, and encouragement for others to speak their minds. The author had the privilege of working with him on various issues and admired his collaborative and candid leadership style. Born in the Jim Crow South, Hastings began his career as a civil rights lawyer, focusing on desegregating public spaces in south Florida. His commitment to public service will be remembered as an example for future generations. The author expresses deep sadness and offers condolences to the Congressman's family.